article.linkText: Wilson scores 19 as UT Arlington takes down Seattle 82-62
article.story: SEATTLE -- — Shemar Wilson had 19 points in UT Arlington's 82-62 victory over Seattle U on Thursday. Wilson added seven rebounds for the Mavericks (16-13, 11-7 Western Athletic Conference). Aaron Cash added 18 points while going 5 of 10 from the floor, including 3 for 5 from 3-point range, and 5 for 7 from the line, and they also had 12 rebounds. Phillip Russell had 13 points and was 3 of 10 shooting, including 1 for 6 from 3-point range, and went 6 for 6 from the line. Cameron Tyson led the Redhawks (18-11, 11-7) in scoring, finishing with 32 points. John Christofilis added seven points for Seattle. Up next for UT Arlington is a Saturday matchup with Utah Valley on the road. Seattle visits Abilene Christian on Thursday. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
